ate surface density at a\nfixed $M_*$ and $\\Sigma_*$. Our results are consistent with the scenario that\nthe local metallicities in galaxies are shaped by the combination of the local\nstars formed in the history and the metal loss caused by galactic winds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Oct 2018 10:29:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-05"}
